{% extends "boilerplate/base.njk" %}

{% block content %}
<section class="section">
    <div class="-l-layout2">
        <div class="imgWrapper">
            <img src="/assets/IMG_6764.jpg" alt="Clean, staged living space prepared for listing">
        </div>
        <div class="container spread">
            <h1>Preparing Homes for Market</h1>
            <h2 class="-t-h2Small">Real Estate Renovation and Property Prep Services in Ottawa</h2>
            <p>Hughes Home Services Ottawa provides pre-sale property preparation services for real estate agents and homeowners in Ottawa and surrounding areas. We support listings by completing repairs, updates, and improvements that help homes present well to buyers and move through the selling process more smoothly.</p>
            <p>This service is intended for properties being prepared for professional photography, open houses, and final listing.</p>
            <a class="-b-spec-3" href="/contact#form">Request a Pre-Listing Consultation</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section narrowSection2 bgContrast2">
    <div class="container spread">
        <h2>Why Pre-Sale Preparation Matters</h2>
        <p>In a competitive market, presentation and condition directly affect buyer interest. Homes that are clean, functional, and visually consistent are easier to market and easier for buyers to evaluate.</p>
        <p>Pre-sale home preparation improves first impressions during showings, reduces buyer objections tied to visible repairs, supports pricing confidence, and keeps listings on schedule without last-minute delays.</p>
    </div>
</section>


<section class="section -l-3col_spread_card_card">
    <div class="spread">
        <h2>Services for Real Estate Agents and Sellers</h2>
        <p>Hughes Home Services Ottawa provides renovation and property preparation work that sits between a standard handyman and a full construction company. We handle small to medium-scale projects that are often needed before a home goes on the market.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cardContainer">
        <div class="card -c-design2 blockedSection4 bgContrast2 dropshadow1 spread ">
            <h3>Interior Updates and Repairs</h3>
            <p>Interior painting and touch-ups, minor repairs and finishing work, kitchen and bathroom updates, flooring repair or replacement, and lighting upgrades with fixture installation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card -c-design2 blockedSection4 bgContrast2 dropshadow1 spread">
            <h3>Exterior and Curb Appeal Work</h3>
            <p>Exterior painting, deck repair or replacement, property and landscape cleanup, tree and hedge trimming, plus stonework and walkway repair.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card -c-design2 blockedSection4 bgContrast2 dropshadow1 spread">
            <h3>Organization and Functionality</h3>
            <p>Garage and basement organization, door and trim alignment, hardware adjustments, and safety-related fixes that help buyers focus on the home itself.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card -c-design2 blockedSection4 bgContrast2 dropshadow1 spread">
            <h3>Medium-Scale Renovation Work</h3>
            <p>We also take on projects that exceed typical handyman work, including room improvements or reconfigurations, selective framing and drywall adjustments, window and door replacements, built-in storage, and other medium-sized renovation tasks.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section -l-2col-2 bgContrast2">
    <div class="container spread">
        <h2>Working With Real Estate Timelines</h2>
        <p>We understand that listing schedules are time-sensitive. Our work is planned around the needs of real estate professionals and sellers, with complimentary consultations, scheduling aligned to listing dates and open houses, coordination with photography and staging, and clear communication from start to completion.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container spread">
        <h2>Benefits for Agents and Their Clients</h2>
        <p>When repairs and improvements are handled before listing, sellers gain confidence in the condition of their property, agents can market listings with fewer limitations, and buyers focus on the home rather than outstanding issues. Showings and negotiations tend to move more efficiently, and the property is ready for market when it matters.</p>
    </div>
</section>


<section class="section -l-2col-2">
    <div class="container spread">
        <h2>Next Steps</h2>
        <p>If you are preparing a property for sale or want support on an upcoming listing, get in touch to discuss the scope and timing.</p>
        <a class="-b-spec-3" href="/contact#form">Schedule a Consultation</a>
    </div>
    <address class="container -layout-1Col_card_1">
        <div class="-card-info blockedSection5 bgContrast1 dropshadow1">
